A man was fatally shot during a verbal altercation late Saturday night in Uptown, according to Minneapolis police. No arrest has been made. Police said they responded just before midnight to a report of shots fired in the area of Hennepin and Lagoon avenues south. They found a man in his early 30s near Girard and Lagoon with a gunshot wound. He died later at the scene, a police spokesman said. You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
